===Acronym===
'''POJ'''

# POJ (Pe̍h-ōe-jī, [[白話字]], [[白话字]]) is an [[wikipedia:orthography|orthography]] in the [[wikipedia:Latin alphabet|Latin alphabet]] created and introduced to [[wikipedia:Taiwan|Taiwan]] by [[wikipedia:Presbyterian|Presbyterian]] [[wikipedia:missionaries|missionaries]] in the 19th century. POJ is a popular orthography for the [[wikipedia:Taiwanese (linguistics)|Taiwanese language]], and [[wikipedia:Min nan|Min nan]] in general.  A version exists for [[wikipedia:Hakka (linguistics)|Hakka]] and is particularly well-suited for the Siyen dialect.